ce:section.ce:para:
Electrochemical synthesis of carbon quantum dots was carried out according to the following procedure: In a beaker of 200mL it was added 150mL of 1-propanol and 12mL of deionized water. Then, 1.45g of KOH was added, yielding a final concentration of 0.16molL−1. The mixture was sonicated for 20min. and two platinum electrodes (Pt) of 4cm2 were introduced in propanol solution containing KOH, along with a Ag/AgCl reference electrode. The distance between the platinum electrodes was kept at approximately 1.5cm (Fig. 1
                        ). After this procedure, it was applied at the working electrode, a constant potential of 6.5V together with a current of 100mA. The samples of the C-dots, in solution, were collected after 4.5h and 8.5h of synthesis, exhibiting a yellow color and a light brown color, respectively (Fig. 2
                        ). Such samples were here denoted C-dot-4.5 and C-dot-8.5.
